                "invention-title": [
                    "Method for improving abrasion resistance of 60NiTi alloy through high-power pulse magnetron sputtering DLC film layer",
                    "一种利用高功率脉冲磁控溅射DLC膜层提高60NiTi合金耐磨性的方法"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention provides a method for improving the abrasion resistance of 60NiTi alloy through a high-power pulse magnetron sputtering DLC film layer, and belongs to the technical field of alloy surface treatment. According to the method, Ti is used as a target material, and a Ti transition layer is obtained through first high-power pulse magnetron sputtering. According to the method, mixed gas of ethylene and high-purity argon is adopted as gas for second high-power pulse magnetron sputtering, argon is responsible for providing high-energy ions to generate plasma, ethylene serves as a carbon source of the DLC film layer and provides a hydrogen element, and under the action of high-power pulse magnetron sputtering, the smooth and compact DLC film is deposited; the friction coefficient of the 60NiTi alloy can be effectively reduced, the hardness of the 60NiTi alloy is improved, and the 60NiTi alloy can serve as a novel bearing material with the low friction coefficient and the high hardness."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明提供了一种利用高功率脉冲磁控溅射DLC膜层提高60NiTi合金耐磨性的方法，属于合金表面处理技术领域。本发明以Ti为靶材，通过第一高功率脉冲磁控溅射，获得Ti过渡层。本发明采用乙烯、高纯氩气的混合气体作为第二高功率脉冲磁控溅射的气体，其中氩气负责提供高能离子产生等离子体，乙烯作为DLC膜层的碳源并且提供氢元素，在高功率脉冲磁控溅射的作用下，沉积出光滑致密的DLC薄膜，能够有效降低60NiTi合金的摩擦系数，提高60NiTi合金的硬度，能够作为低摩擦系数、高硬度的新型轴承材料。"
                }
            ]
        }
